Name: timestamp
Comment: Time elapsed since the controller was started [s]

Name: actual_TCP_pose
Comment: Actual Cartesian coordinates of the tool: (x,y,z,rx,ry,rz), where rx, ry and rz is a rotation vector representation of the tool orientation

Name: actual_TCP_speed
Comment: Actual speed of the tool given in Cartesian coordinates. The speed is given in [m/s] and the rotational part of the TCP speed (rx, ry, rz) is the angular velocity given in [rad/s]

Name: actual_TCP_force
Comment: Generalized forces in the TCP. It compensates the measurement for forces and torques generated by the payload

Name: target_TCP_pose
Comment: Target Cartesian coordinates of the tool: (x,y,z,rx,ry,rz), where rx, ry and rz is a rotation vector representation of the tool orientation

Name: target_TCP_speed
Comment: Target speed of the tool given in Cartesian coordinates. The speed is given in [m/s] and the rotational part of the TCP speed (rx, ry, rz) is the angular velocity given in [rad/s]

Name: actual_digital_input_bits
Comment: Current state of the digital inputs. 0-7: Standard, 8-15: Configurable, 16-17: Tool

Name: joint_temperatures
Comment: Temperature of each joint in degrees Celsius

Name: actual_tool_accelerometer
Comment: Tool x, y and z accelerometer values

Name: speed_scaling
Comment: Speed scaling of the trajectory limiter

Name: actual_digital_output_bits
Comment: Current state of the digital outputs. 0-7: Standard, 8-15: Configurable, 16-17: Tool

Name: elbow_position
Comment: Position of robot elbow in Cartesian Base Coordinates

Name: elbow_velocity
Comment: Velocity of robot elbow in Cartesian Base Coordinates

Name: robot_status_bits
Comment: Bits 0-3:  Is power on | Is program running | Is teach button pressed | Is power button pressed

Name: safety_status_bits
Comment: Bits 0-10: Is normal mode | Is reduced mode | Is protective stopped | Is recovery mode | Is safeguard stopped | Is system emergency stopped | Is robot emergency stopped | Is emergency stopped | Is violation | Is fault | Is stopped due to safety

Name: analog_io_types
Comment: Bits 0-3: analog input 0 | analog input 1 | analog output 0 | analog output 1, {0=current[mA], 1=voltage[V]}

Name: output_bit_register_X (X=[64 .. 127])
Comment: 64 general purpose bits X: [64..127] - The upper range of the boolean output registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).
X: [0..23] - The lower range of the integer output registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.
X: [24..47] - The upper range of the integer output registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).
X: [0..23] - The lower range of the double output registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.
X: [24..47] - The upper range of the double output registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).

Name: input_bit_registers0_to_31
Comment: General purpose bits (input read back) This range of the boolean output registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.

Name: input_bit_registers32_to_63
Comment: General purpose bits (input read back) This range of the boolean output registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.

Name: input_bit_register_X  (X=[64 .. 127])
Comment: 64 general purpose bits X: [64..127] - The upper range of the boolean output registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).
X: [0..23] - The lower range of the integer input registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.
X: [24..47] - The upper range of the integer input registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).
X: [0..23] - The lower range of the double input registers is reserved for FieldBus/PLC interface usage.
X: [24..47] - The upper range of the double input registers can be used by external RTDE clients (i.e URCAPS).

Name: tool_digital_output0_mode
Comment: The current mode of digital output 0

Name: tool_digital_output1_mode
Comment: The current mode of digital output 1

Name: payload_cog
Comment: Payload Center of Gravity (CoGx, CoGy, CoGz) m

Name: payload_inertia
Comment: Payload inertia matrix elements (Ixx,Iyy,Izz,Ixy,Ixz,Iyz] expressed in kg*m^2

Name: script_control_line
Comment: Script line number that is actually in control of the robot given the robot is locked by one of the threads in the script. If no thread is locking the robot this field is set to '0'. Script line number should not be confused with program tree line number displayed on polyscope.

Name: ft_raw_wrench
Comment: Raw force and torque measurement, not compensated for forces and torques caused by the payload
